cs.NI, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CV, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper discusses the challenges and feasibility of creating a ubiquitous indoor positioning system, which involves networking, human-computer interaction, and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of crowd-sourcing and cloud computing, which falls under the categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of sensors in cell phones for floor plan generation suggests the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision), and the processing and storage of data falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
